All tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Problem:** `_find_stale_evidence_paths` in `scripts/task_manifest.py` produced a false-positive `stale_evidence_artifact` warning when evidence referenced an absolute path (e.g., `/tmp/.../real_artifact.log`). The regex `_EVIDENCE_PATH_RE` has a negative lookbehind `(?<![:/])` that prevents matching after `/`, so it matched `mp/.../real_artifact.log` (dropping the leading `/t`). When resolved against `base_dir`, this created a wrong (nonexistent) path.

**Fix:** After extracting the matched path, walk backwards from the match position through valid path characters (`a-zA-Z0-9_.-/`) to recover the complete path. If the recovered path starts with `/`, resolve it as absolute (`Path(full_p)`); otherwise resolve against `base_dir` as before.

**File changed:** `scripts/task_manifest.py` — `_find_stale_evidence_paths` function (lines 219-246), 8 lines added, no other changes.

**Verification:**
• `python3 -m unittest scripts.test_task_manifest -q` — 24 tests pass (including the previously failing `test_evidence_references_existing_artifact_path_no_warning`)
• `python3 scripts/preseed_session_plan.py --test` — passes
• Manual smoke test confirms absolute paths, relative paths, and nonexistent paths all handled correctly
